The United States strongly condemns the recent terrorist attacks in Yemen, which killed over 130 people and injured hundreds more. The attacks, carried out during Friday prayers, highlight the depravity of the terrorists and the threat they pose to Yemen, the region, and the world. The United States expresses its condolences to the families and loved ones of the victims. The airstrikes on the Presidential Palace in Aden and the attacks on the legitimate government of Yemen are also condemned. The United States urges all parties in Yemen to cease unilateral and offensive military actions and instead seek a peaceful political solution. It calls for a return to political dialogue and a commitment to a peaceful political transition in accordance with various agreements and resolutions.